Covariances - BNL, July, 2011: Covariances were adopted from      8325 1451
COMMARA-2.0, where BNL performed new evaluation of covariances in 8325 1451
the full energy range in 2010. In thermal and resolved resonance  8325 1451
region we made use of the covariance formalism based on kernel    8325 1451
approximation along with data in the Atlas of Neutron Resonances. 8325 1451
Elastic scattering uncertainty was largely determined by potential8325 1451
scattering contribution via the uncertainty of the scattering     8325 1451
radius R'.                                                        8325 1451
                                                                  8325 1451
In fast neutron region up to 20 MeV covariance estimates were     8325 1451
produced using the nuclear reaction code EMPIRE and the Bayesian  8325 1451
code KALMAN. The KALMAN code along with selected experimental     8325 1451
data was used to determine the correlation matrix of the model    8325 1451
parameters. Furthermore, additional parameters scaling total      8325 1451
and absorption cross section were included to prevent the         8325 1451
unrealistic drop in the cross-section uncertainties and,          8325 1451
in some cases, to cover spread of experimental data. The          8325 1451
elastic cross-section uncertainties were computed as              8325 1451
difference of total and absorption reaction channel.              8325 1451
